Formalized question 1 of the 1982 IMO

modified the domain of f to be Nat rather than PNat - as proving inequalities and such with PNat is more tedious.

You seem to have also PR'd Q3, can you move that to a separate PR?
Are you planning to reopen this as a new PR? Despite my remarks, the main argument seemed correct, it just requires some tweaking.
Hi, yes sorry! I am moving it to another PR - I made a mistake when making a new branch and the PR. I also made the appropriate tweaks.
I don't think the proof can be considered to be correct as is. Please update the problem statement to the correct domain.
You should state the problem in terms of `f : ℕ+ → ℕ`. We are trying to be formal here, aren't we?
I don't see why proving inequalities on `ℕ+` would be any more complicated. If you have any questions, feel free to ask on Zulip.
This lemma doesn't make sense. In the original problem, `f 0` isn't even defined, so making use of its value is something we shouldn't be doing.
